<title>Exercises</title>
<p><term>Note: </term>For programming exercises, first draw 
a UML class diagram describing all classes and
their inheritance relationships and/or associations.
</p>

<ol>
<li><p>Explain the difference between the following pairs of terms:</p>
    <ol>
        <li> <p>Representation and action</p></li>
        <li> <p>Binary operator and unary operation</p></li>
        <li> <p>Class constant and class variable</p></li>
        <li> <p>Helper method and class method</p></li>
        <li> <p>Operator overloading and method overloading</p></li>
        <li> <p>Method call and method composition</p></li>
        <li> <p>Type conversion and type promotion</p></li>
    </ol>
</li>
<li>
    <p> For each of the following data types, list
        how many bits are used in its representation and how many values can
        be represented:
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li>  <c>int</c></li>
        <li>  <c>char</c></li>
        <li>  <c>byte</c></li>
        <li>  <c>long</c></li>
        <li>  <c>double</c></li>
    </ol>
</li>
<li>
