    <ol>
        <li><p>  Methods and variables that are associated with
        a class rather than with its instances must be declared __________.</p></li>
        <li><p>  When an operation involves values of two different types,
        one value must be __________ before the expression can be evaluated.</p></li>
        <li><p>  Constants should be declared __________.</p></li>
        <li><p>  Variables that take <c>true</c> and <c>false</c> as their
        possible values are known as __________.</p></li>
